.TH CITRIXSCAN 1 "March 2026" "1.0.0" "CitrixScan Manual"
.SH NAME
citrixscan \- full-scope external security scanner for Citrix NetScaler ADC/Gateway
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B citrixscan
.RI [ targets ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B citrixscan
performs comprehensive, non-exploitative security assessments of
internet-facing Citrix NetScaler ADC and NetScaler Gateway appliances.
.PP
It identifies firmware versions using 10 detection vectors, maps them
against 25 known CVEs (2019\-2026), detects indicators of compromise,
audits for security misconfigurations, and checks TLS configurations.
.PP
All checks are unauthenticated and production-safe. No payloads are sent.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B targets
Target IPs or hostnames (space-separated).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read targets from file (one per line, # for comments).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
HTTPS port (default: 443).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timeout " " \fISEC\fR
Timeout per request in seconds (default: 15).
.TP
.BR \-\-threads " " \fIN\fR
Concurrent scan threads (default: 5).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output\-json " " \fIFILE\fR
Write JSON report to FILE.
.TP
.BR \-\-csv " " \fIFILE\fR
Write CSV report to FILE.
.TP
.BR \-\-markdown " " \fIFILE\fR
Write Markdown report to FILE.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose output (paths, ETags, TLS details, security headers).
.TP
.BR \-\-modules " " \fILIST\fR
Comma-separated scan modules: all, cve, ioc, misconfig, tls, headers (default: all).
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-deep
Skip EPA binary download for faster scanning.
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-cves
Print the CVE database and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan a single target:
.B citrixscan 10.0.0.1 -v
.TP
Multiple targets with reports:
.B citrixscan 10.0.0.1 10.0.0.2 -o report.json --csv report.csv
.TP
Bulk scan from file:
.B citrixscan -f targets.txt --threads 10 -o results.json
.TP
List CVE database:
.B citrixscan --list-cves
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Scan completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Error in arguments or target file not found.
